          <p class="supertitle">Full Time / Hollywood, CA</p>
  <h1>Senior Backend Rails Developer</h1>

  <div class="columns generic ">
    <div class="column main">
      <p>We’re a small, focused startup about to come out of closed Beta making a killer desktop app for the music industry. Think Dropbox + Lightroom + YouSendIt.</p>

<p>Our application runs on the desktop, but a lot of the magic happens in the cloud. We use Rails/Mongoid/MongoDB to provide backend API services for the client, and also to serve up our website. We’re looking for a talented Rails developer who is capable and passionate about taking on a wide variety of challenges.</p>

<p>Your work might involve building the consumer-facing side of the web application, working with the internal APIs used by our desktop client, devising a migration strategy for schema objects, or even building out a public API for external developers.  We’re working at a breakneck pace adding cool new features and growing our userbase &ndash; so we’re looking for someone who can handle anything that’s thrown at them.</p>

<p>We&rsquo;re still in beta, so you’ll be able to get in at the ground floor and have a huge impact.</p>

<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Experience building and scaling successful web applications using Rails</li>
<li>Great, in-depth knowledge of Ruby</li>
<li>Ability to work effectively with web designers</li>
<li>Good knowledge of encryption</li>
</ul>


<p><strong>Pluses</strong></p>

<ul>
<li>Javascript, C++</li>
<li>MongoDB or NoSQL</li>
</ul>


<p><strong>Please don’t judge us by our placeholder website – it’s all programmer art! Our designers are almost done with a new version that won’t make your eyeballs bleed.</strong></p>
</div><!-- /.column.main -->

